  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7117 sitting just above the max negative gamma strike at 7115, dealers are in active buying mode to hedge their short gamma exposure, creating upward pressure on the index. The massive positive gamma wall at 7200 (+8.39B) will force dealers to aggressively sell into any rally approaching that level, making it a critical resistance zone with significant hedging flow anticipated. The PIN regime with 65.8B total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting behavior, with dealers providing liquidity by buying dips toward 7100 and selling rallies toward 7150-7200.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect upward drift toward 7150-7200 resistance with dealers capping moves higher.",
